1.INTRODUCTION

There are 2 seperate tasks given and each task includes some sub-parts. In the first task includes 3 seperate subtasks. - In a part of first task, i observed one instance from each classes considering X,Y,Z axis and total form of XYZ axis. In the first class of a part of 1. task, I plotted data belonging each axis both without cumulative sum and with cumulative sum. But for the other classes, i observed XYZ plot of data without cumulative sum and cumulative sum data of plot belonging each axis and total form of xyz axis. Additionally, for this subtasks codes can be seen in the code section. I added only first class codes. The only thing i changed to find other classes is to change the numbers(from 1 to 8)

  • In b part of first task,first thing that i did is to filter each test classes X,Y and Z axis and after cumulative sum take the last column which is the point that the instance is situated. Then i combined X,Y and Z axis for each class. After that, i created a basic for loop" and combined train and test data for each class XYZ axis. Then, I found euclidean and manhattan distances.In order not to make my computer slower, i only demonstrated the first test class euclidean and manhattan distances. I repeated it for 8 times since the number of class is 8. But you can find only fist class codes in the code section. Since actually what i did is the same nearly. The only difference is to change class number(from 1 to 8). Then, i filtered each training classes X,Y and Z axis and after cumulative sum take the last column which is the point that the instance is situated. Then i combined X,Y and Z axis for each class. I created knn algorithm with 10 fold cross validation to determine the best value of k.

  • In c part of first task, I predicted test data that i had created by using rbind function and prepared confusion matrix and gave some information and comments.

In the second task includes 4 seperate subtasks.

  • In the a part of second task, I trained a logistic regression model on the training data using fused lasso penalties.I used predict function to predict the test data and tried to create confusion matrix.

  • In the b part of second task, according to the regression coefficients that i found, I plotted to see some interesting information and tried to interpret.

  • In the c part of second task,i took difference between time series by using diff function. Then, i repeated the a part.

  • In the d part of second task, according to the regression coefficients that i found in c part, I plotted to see some interesting information and tried to interpret.
